cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for automatic localization of anatomical structures in medical images using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the ConvNet, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of spatial pyramid pooling suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with medical images, which suggests the involvement of multimedia, falling under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of ConvNets suggests the involvement of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
